questions.question:
What does `extends` do with interfaces?

```ts
interface Animal { name: string; }
interface Dog extends Animal { breed: string; }
```

What is an index signature in an interface?

```ts
interface StringMap {
  [key: string]: number;
}
```

What error does this produce?

```ts
interface User {
  readonly id: number;
  name: string;
}
const user: User = { id: 1, name: 'Alice' };
user.id = 2;
```

What does this interface describe?

```ts
interface Printable {
  print(): void;
}
```

What does this code demonstrate?

```ts
interface Config {
  debug: boolean;
}
interface Config {
  verbose: boolean;
}
const cfg: Config = { debug: true, verbose: false };
```

What does this interface allow?

```ts
interface NumberArray {
  [index: number]: string;
}
```

What is wrong with this code?

```ts
interface Person {
  name: string;
  age: number;
}
const p: Person = { name: 'Alice' };
```

What does this code output?

```ts
interface Greeter {
  (name: string): string;
}
const greet: Greeter = (name) => `Hello, ${name}`;
console.log(greet('World'));
```

Does this code compile?

```ts
interface HasName { name: string; }
const obj = { name: 'Alice', age: 30 };
const person: HasName = obj;
```

What happens with excess property checking on object literals?

```ts
interface Point { x: number; y: number; }
const p: Point = { x: 1, y: 2, z: 3 };
```

What does this interface describe?

```ts
interface Pair<T, U> {
  first: T;
  second: U;
}
```
